    <Question>
        <QuestionIdentifier>Q1</QuestionIdentifier>
        <DisplayName>Initial Intruction</DisplayName>
        <IsRequired>true</IsRequired>
        <QuestionContent>
            <FormattedContent><![CDATA[
                <p>
                Imagine you are playing a creative game in a 3-D world. You will be playing one of the following roles during each hit.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Architect</li>
                    <li>Builder</li>
                </ul>
                <p>As an <b> Architect </b>, you will instruct an imaginary builder to build a given structure in a 3-D voxel world environment. 
                You will be shown: the target structure and a partially built structure.
                You are being asked to describe in plain text, how to get from the intermediate structure towards having the final structure.
                Make sure your instructions are understandable, succint, and in English.
                Please know that a builder will follow your instruction blindly without seeing a target structure and will have 45 seconds to complete the task. 
                The builder will only have access to your instruction, the picture of the intermediate stage of the structure, and 45 seconds to execute the instructions.
                </p>
                <p>As a <b> Builder </b>, you will need to build what is instructed in the given instruction set in 45 seconds.
                You would need use <b>'w/a/s/d'</b> to move <b>'forward/left/back/right'</b>,
                <b>'space'</b> to jump, <b>'double space'</b> to fly, <b>'shift'</b> to return to ground after flying
                and <b>'esc'</b> to leave the world and back to the website.
                </p>
                <h3> This is how the Builder will look in action:</h3>
                <img src="https://iglumturkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/qualification-test/demo.gif" alt="Builder demo"/>
                <br></br>
                <p>The following questions will give you a glimpse of both roles. Please select appropriate answers.</p>
                <p>Click on <b>"Submit Test" </b> button at the bottom once you have complted answering all questions.</p>
                <br></br>
                <p><b>Questions 1-5 are based on the role for an Architect with the below target structure given. Please select the most appropriate instructions to build the structure.</b></p>
                <img src="https://iglumturkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/qualification-test/iglu-q1.png" alt="Target structure"/>
            ]]></FormattedContent>
            <Text>1. What would be an appropriate first instruction you would provide to the builder?</Text>
        </QuestionContent>
        <AnswerSpecification>
            <SelectionAnswer>
                <StyleSuggestion>radiobutton</StyleSuggestion>
                <Selections>
                    <Selection>
                        <SelectionIdentifier>right</SelectionIdentifier>
                        <Text>Facing east, make a tower with a blue block at bottom, green block on top of that and then a blue block on top</Text>
                    </Selection>
                    <Selection>
                        <SelectionIdentifier>wrong1</SelectionIdentifier>
                        <Text>Facing east, make a tower consisting of two blocks with a blue block at the bottom</Text>
                    </Selection>
                    <Selection>
                        <SelectionIdentifier>wrong2</SelectionIdentifier>
                        <Text>Facing north, make a tower consisting of two blocks with a red block at the bottom</Text>
                    </Selection>
                    <Selection>
                        <SelectionIdentifier>wrong3</SelectionIdentifier>
                        <Text>Put a green block on top of yellow one while facing north</Text>
                    </Selection>
                </Selections>
            </SelectionAnswer>
        </AnswerSpecification>
    </Question>
